================================================================================
File Format Specification References
================================================================================

PolyDoc reads and writes documents in formats defined by the following
published specifications. These specifications are referenced for
interoperability; their inclusion here does not imply endorsement by the
respective standards bodies or companies.

  * ECMA-376 (Office Open XML File Formats) / ISO/IEC 29500
      ECMA International — https://ecma-international.org/publications-and-standards/standards/ecma-376/
      Used for: DOCX read/write support.

  * [MS-DOC]: Word (.doc) Binary File Format
      Microsoft Open Specification Promise — https://docs.microsoft.com/openspecs/office_file_formats/ms-doc/
      Used for: legacy DOC ingest (reference only; no binary reproduction).

  * OWPML (Open Word Processor Markup Language) / KS X 6101
      한국산업표준 (Korean Industrial Standard) — https://standard.go.kr/
      Used for: HWPX read/write support.

  * HWP 5.0 Binary File Format Specification
      본 제품은 한글과컴퓨터의 HWP 문서 파일(.hwp) 공개 문서를 참고하여
      개발하였습니다.
      Used for: HWP 5.x binary ingest (reference only; no binary reproduction).

